  "text": "Cultures were carried out in 35-mm Lux suspension culture dishes (No. 171099, Nunc, Naperville, IL, USA), as reported elsewhere. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] One milliliter of culture contained 200 sorted cells, 1.2% of 1500 centipoise methylcellulose (MTC, Shinetsu Chemical, Tokyo, Japan), 30% FCS, 1% deionized fraction V bovine serum albumin (BSA, Sigma Chemical, St Louis, MO, USA), 5 × 10 −5 mol/l 2-mercaptoethanol (2-ME, Sigma), and various combinations of CSFs. Final concentrations of each CSF were as follows: IL-3, 10 ng/ml; GM-CSF, 10 ng/ml; G-CSF, 20 ng/ml; Epo, 2 U/ml; SCF, 20 ng/ml. These concentrations supported maximal total colony formation in preliminary titration experiments (data not shown).",
